AD_FIELD.NAME: Temperature
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Temperature of the agent, value between 0 and 2
AD_FIELD.HELP:
In the context of a Large Language Model (LLM) that is used by the agent, "temperature" is a parameter that controls the randomness of the model's responses:
Low temperature (e.g., 0.1): Produces more predictable and conservative outputs. High temperature (e.g., 1.0 or higher): Produces more random and creative outputs.
Temperature adjusts the probability distribution for selecting the next word in a sequence, balancing between coherence and creativity.

Adds an HQL statement to model the data to be sent. This HQL will be evaluated and its results will be exported in a .csv file. - Query Requirement: You must use the alias e for the main entity (e.g., from Product e) because the system automatically appends security filters (Client/Org) using that specific alias.
Output Formats:
- CSV: Returns a comma-separated list. Includes headers if you use aliases in the select statement. - Plain Text (Non-CSV): Returns data in Property: Value format. Records are separated by double line breaks (\n\n).
- Full Entities: If selecting the whole object (select e), it returns a structured string containing all readable properties.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Temperature
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Temperature of the agent, value between 0 and 2
AD_FIELD.HELP:
In the context of a Large Language Model (LLM) that is used by the agent, "temperature" is a parameter that controls the randomness of the model's responses:
Low temperature (e.g., 0.1): Produces more predictable and conservative outputs. High temperature (e.g., 1.0 or higher): Produces more random and creative outputs.
Temperature adjusts the probability distribution for selecting the next word in a sequence, balancing between coherence and creativity.
